BREAKING NEWS: Maryland @GovLarryHogan says Maryland has achieved the 14-day trend of plateauing or downward trend in regards to coronavirus cases.

Effective Friday, May 15 at 5 p.m., the stay-at-home order in Maryland will be transitioned to a safer-at-home guidance. https://t.co/mNXduXrDxu
